**Landscape Design Research "Forming Atmosphere"** featured in Brian Osborn. 2018 "Coding Behaviour." *In Codify: Parametric and Computational Design in Landscape Architecture*, edited by Bradley Cantrell and Adam Mekies, 180–95. Milton Park, Abingdon, Oxon, New York, NY: Routledge.

2015

**Lhasa VR: Visualizing The Historic Tibetan Capital**

University of Virginia, Charlottesville, Virginia

Role: Research Associate and GIS specialist

Collaborating with scholars from the UVA’s Tibet Center, I digitized and geo-referenced several important historical maps for Lhasa, the capital city of Tibet, using geospatial and virtual reality technologies. This work greatly contributed to the Tibetan and Himalayan Library’s Places Database, the largest and most authoritative database of the Tibetan region in the world. 

Germano David, Shaeffer, Kurtis, Huang, Guoping, Rourk, Will, Weinberger, Steven, **Zhang, Zihao**, 2015 Transforming Lhasa: a virtual reality tour of historic Lhasa**. **Featured in: [https://magazine.arts.virginia.edu/stories/lhasa-vr-visualizing-the-historic-tibetan-capital](https://magazine.arts.virginia.edu/stories/lhasa-vr-visualizing-the-historic-tibetan-capital)  

